Risk Assessment: 

Potential risk: +
1) Tripping or falling +
2) Ball rolling off and getting underfoot +
3) Small balls used in some parts of the experiment being swallowed

Solution: +
1) Demonstrator must emphasise that children must walk, should stop
everyone walking to actually do explanations +
2) Must be made very clear to children that they may not kick or throw
the balls ever +
3) Do not use small balls parts of experiment for audiences of very
young children

